sentences: Irina Emeliantseva (Russian: Ирина Емельянцева) (born 26 September 1973 in Seltso, Bryansk Oblast, Russia)  is a Russian composer of orchestral works and chamber music in different cast and pianist.

In addition, they received numerous fellowships, stays (composer in residence at the Künstlerhof Schreyahn the Ministry of Culture of Niedersachsen, Castle Wiepersdorf etc.) and commissions (e.g. European Music Summer in Berlin, composition "light splitter" Apocalypse for the ensemble "New vocalist" Berlin) and many more.
Gartow-Foundation Award for young composers in Germany (1995)
Composer Award at the Sound Ways Festival in St Petersburg (1996)
